The '''Mark 26 nuclear bomb''' was related to the [[Mark 21 nuclear bomb|Mark 21]]. Development of the Mk-26 started on 1 September 1954. At the end of July 1955 the design of the Mk-21 was released for production, while the design for the Mk-26 was not. The "Clean" Mk-21C which was tested in the [[Operation Redwing|Redwing Navajo]] shot did not interest the [[US Air Force]], or [[United States Atomic Energy Commission|AEC]]. As the decision not to pursue the "clean" Mk-21 closely coincided with the decision to terminate development of the Mk-26 in April 1957, it is possible that Mk-26 was the designation for the clean version of the Mk-21.

