{{Infobox company | name = RiverSync, Inc | logo = [[File:RiverSync-Logo.svg|250px|RiverSync Logo]] | type = [[Private company|Private]] | foundation = {{start date and age|2012}} | location_city = [[Bangkok]] | location_country = [[Thailand]] | area_served = Worldwide | industry = [[Data center]] | products = Frigo | homepage = {{url|http://riversync.com/|riversync.com}} }}
'''RiverSync''' is a Thai corporation headquartered in Bangkok, Thailand. RiverSync sells converged [[Micro Data Center|micro data center]], modular data center, and physical infrastructure equipment that enable businesses to rapidly deploy their computing infrastructure with prefabricated environment. RiverSync target markets including large companies and small and medium-sized businesses across various markets.
RiverSync has around 200 employees, competing against [[Schneider Electric|Schneider]], Rittal, [[Emerson Electric|Emerson]], and [[Panduit]].
==History== RiverSync, founded in 2012 by Sarin Na Wangkanai, Vitool Songwattana, and Veerayuth Punnium,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://riversync.com/About/Leadership|title=Leadership - RiverSync|website=riversync.com|access-date=2016-03-04}}</ref> introduced its micro data center product in 2015 and continued with the development of rack enclosure.
